{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "plugin": ["/ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/acc/plugins/opencode/acc.ts"],
  "command": {
    "goal": {
      "description": "Run an autonomous acc goal loop",
      "template": "Start an acc goal loop for this owner goal:\n\n$ARGUMENTS\n\nUse the configured acc MCP tools in this OpenCode session:\n1. Call `acc_retrieve` with the goal first and cite the relevant [ids].\n2. Call `acc_act` with runtime \"solve\" and the goal. If it returns a `brain_frame`, reason in this session and submit the resolution with `acc_act` runtime \"continue\" using the `frame_id`; end `proposal_text` with a `PREDICT: <0.00-1.00> <why>` calibration line, which acc strips before the owner sees it.\n3. Do the actual work, recursively using `acc_retrieve`/`acc_act` when memory or judgment is missing. Do not introduce a second reasoner or background agent.\n4. Persist autonomously through routine blockers: inspect, edit, run commands, fix failures, and verify. Stop only for owner-held facts, consent/security boundaries, or external actions requiring authority.\n5. Record `acc_act` runtime \"outcome\" against the commitment with verification evidence, then report the result, cited [ids], and any clean blocker."
    }
  },
  "mcp": {
    "acc": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": ["acc", "mcp"],
      "enabled": true,
      "timeout": 300000,
      "environment": {
        "ACC_MCP_CALL_DEADLINE_SECS": "45"
      }
    }
  }
}
